1
00:00:15,530 --> 00:00:20,080
Your heart returning back to May of that year

2
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:22,910
is not a strange thing at all.

3
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:29,170
Even if you lose an umbrella that you cherish,

4
00:00:29,170 --> 00:00:32,910
you think about that umbrella every time it rains.

5
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:44,240
Let alone,

6
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:50,860
if the season you lost your loved one returns each year...

7
00:00:56,470 --> 00:00:58,320
of course,

8
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:03,670
our heart goes back to that time.

9
00:01:03,670 --> 00:01:05,870
Just as if it happened yesterday.

10
00:01:09,220 --> 00:01:12,840
Sir, I'm sorry to interrupt, but...

11
00:01:30,730 --> 00:01:32,380
Yes.

12
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:36,190
Did you get my text message?

13
00:01:39,110 --> 00:01:41,130
We found them.

14
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:57,080
[Episode 12: The First May]

15
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:24,730
Sorry! Sorry!

16
00:02:24,730 --> 00:02:28,130
Please, save me!

17
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:34,300
Here! There's a kid over here!

18
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,350
Oh, my!

19
00:02:52,350 --> 00:02:54,020
Don't look at it!

20
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:58,760
Your writing is so small that I can't see it anyway.

21
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:03,170
What's the point of writing it so small when we're going to read it to each other anyway?

22
00:03:03,170 --> 00:03:05,470
Can't we forego the prayer?

23
00:03:05,470 --> 00:03:07,990
Isn't the exchange of vows enough?

24
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:12,390
There's no officiant or guests.

25
00:03:12,390 --> 00:03:15,370
And we didn't prepare outfits, wedding gifts, or anything.

26
00:03:15,370 --> 00:03:18,010
We need to exchange something for our wedding.

27
00:03:18,010 --> 00:03:20,720
I'm not good at writing long texts.

28
00:03:21,270 --> 00:03:23,640
Who said to write something long?

29
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:25,200
Just write your expectations.

30
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:31,580
The power of our prayers is probably really good because He feels bad about us marrying with nothing.

31
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:34,860
What about you, Hee Tae? Why aren't you writing anything?

32
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:39,550
I already memorized it. There's a prayer that I say every day.

33
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:42,500
What do you pray for?

34
00:03:44,510 --> 00:03:46,480
When I die...

35
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:51,390
I want you to be buried with me.

36
00:03:51,390 --> 00:03:54,900
As in buried alive with you? Pray for something else!

37
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:57,060
You said your prayers are powerful!

38
00:03:57,060 --> 00:03:59,660
Then you can pray that you won't be buried alive.

39
00:03:59,660 --> 00:04:03,000
Let's put to test whose prayers are heard.

40
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:20,790
What are you doing in my office?

41
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:35,090
We got a tip that your son is closely connected

42
00:04:35,090 --> 00:04:39,210
to the main suspect of this incident.

43
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:44,470
I think you are mistaken. The suspect only said—

44
00:04:44,470 --> 00:04:48,270
Stop. You can defend yourself during the investigation.

45
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:50,410
An inspector...

46
00:04:51,460 --> 00:04:54,230
should always stay objective.

47
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:59,600
Until the investigation is over, I will take charge of the steering wheel.

48
00:05:13,470 --> 00:05:18,200
All right! Next up, is the exchange of vows from the bride and groom.

49
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:21,010
Starting with the groom.

50
00:05:21,010 --> 00:05:22,670
Yes!

51
00:05:26,090 --> 00:05:31,150
I, Hwang Hee Tae, accept Kim Myeong Hee as my wife.

52
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:35,900
Forever, with love and respect, I will cherish her.

53
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:40,100
I solemnly swear before the Lord.

54
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:47,970
Does the bride, Kim Myeong Hee, who's known to be terrible with words, swear the same?

55
00:05:47,970 --> 00:05:50,000
Yes.

56
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,330
Your voice is too little!

57
00:05:52,330 --> 00:05:54,210
Yes!

58
00:05:54,210 --> 00:05:55,510
That's good.

59
00:05:55,510 --> 00:06:00,080
All right. Then, lastly, the bride and groom will exchange their prayers.

60
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:05,480
I heard that the bride was tormented by the agony of creation.

61
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:07,340
Shall we hear it?

62
00:06:07,340 --> 00:06:10,790
Why doesn't the groom that memorized it already go first?

63
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:16,100
All right.

64
00:06:25,450 --> 00:06:27,110
Lord,

65
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:31,030
no matter what happens,

66
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:36,070
we will not let go of these hands we finally get to hold. I pray we can overcome the hardship.

67
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:40,380
More than anything, I pray that you give me

68
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:43,450
worse pains instead of Myeong Hee.

69
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:48,940
In God's name, I pray.

70
00:06:50,490 --> 00:06:52,040
Amen.

71
00:06:53,330 --> 00:06:55,140
Amen.

72
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:09,090
Darn it. My prayer's sloppy.

73
00:07:09,090 --> 00:07:11,390
You said you'd pray that I be buried alive with you.

74
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:21,170
I, Kim Myeong Hee...

75
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:23,130
Myeong Hee!

76
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,940
Myeong Hee,

77
00:07:27,940 --> 00:07:31,770
your father...

78
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,730
Sister.

79
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,960
No.

80
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,710
That can't be my father.

81
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:06,320
Hee Tae, take a look.

82
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:09,410
My father isn't that small.

83
00:08:51,070 --> 00:08:52,850
Father.

84
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:56,980
Father, wake up.

85
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:59,550
Stop playing around and wake up.

86
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:03,510
It's cold. Why are you laying down like this?

87
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:07,110
Father. Father, wake up!

88
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:10,590
Open your eyes!

89
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,300
How...

90
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:17,870
How could you do this?

91
00:09:19,370 --> 00:09:21,320
Till the end...

92
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:25,940
Why do you make me suffer like this till the end?!

93
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:32,480
No. I can't let you go like this, Father!

94
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,490
Father!

95
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:37,790
Father, let's go home!

96
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:41,190
Let's go home, Father!

97
00:09:50,310 --> 00:09:54,500
Father... Father...

98
00:09:55,190 --> 00:09:59,990
[Name - Kim Seong Wook]
[Age - 18 years old
Lost Son]

99
00:09:59,990 --> 00:10:02,370
So, you're telling me...

100
00:10:02,370 --> 00:10:08,050
our son hasn't died but has been arrested?

101
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:11,920
Oh, my!

102
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:14,090
But...

103
00:10:14,090 --> 00:10:18,720
didn't you say you were arrested with him? How were you released?

104
00:10:21,510 --> 00:10:24,310
I was, w-well...

105
00:10:40,070 --> 00:10:42,110
Brother!

106
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,720
If it's because you feel guilty—

107
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:48,080
Three days.

108
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:53,130
The world I believed in crumbled in just three days.

109
00:10:53,910 --> 00:10:56,500
I was dragged away and treated like an animal.

110
00:10:56,500 --> 00:11:00,390
When I was released alone, thanks to Mr. Hwang and lied down in my bed,

111
00:11:01,330 --> 00:11:03,980
do you know what I thought?

112
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,220
I felt comfortable.

113
00:11:13,830 --> 00:11:18,410
I didn't even know if the people who were arrested with me were dead or alive.

114
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:21,610
But I felt so cozy and comfortable.

115
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:29,430
That's why I feel ashamed.

116
00:11:30,070 --> 00:11:32,340
I'm ashamed of lying down, eating,

117
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:36,460
and even wearing this kind of suit and breathing this air.

118
00:11:36,460 --> 00:11:38,880
I feel like a total coward.

119
00:11:40,490 --> 00:11:43,340
I'm so embarrassed I could die!

120
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:50,380
Brother...

121
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:55,030
there's nothing we can change,

122
00:11:55,030 --> 00:11:57,960
but there are still things we can do.

123
00:12:15,890 --> 00:12:19,440
I'll go find a way to contact your family in Naju

124
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:22,370
and ask about the funeral procedure.

125
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:31,150
Myeong Hee, you stay here by your father's side.

126
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:36,990
I'll take care of all the necessary arrangements.

127
00:12:45,510 --> 00:12:48,050
[From Kim Hyun Chul to Kim Myeong Hee]

128
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:58,060
[Regular savings account]

129
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:05,720
[Current Balance]

130
00:13:26,730 --> 00:13:31,150
Myeong Hee, this is a savings account of the money that you've been sending.

131
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:34,190
It's in your name.

132
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:38,790
All you need to do is take your stamp to find the money.

133
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:44,260
Myeong Soo said this one time...

134
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:46,890
That the runner who runs way in the front

135
00:13:46,890 --> 00:13:50,020
does nothing but block the wind for the others.

136
00:13:50,020 --> 00:13:54,090
He said it was your loss if you stood in the front from the beginning.

137
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:00,160
Perhaps, I lived my life...

138
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:04,520
always in the front blocking the wind with my whole body.

139
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:07,620
I was that runner who was in the front.

140
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:15,180
I was afraid you'd be hit by the wind like me.

141
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:18,560
What if your wings were hurt from the hardships of this world?

142
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:23,930
I hoped you wouldn't stand in the front like me...

143
00:14:23,930 --> 00:14:26,880
and always tried to hold you back.

144
00:14:29,270 --> 00:14:34,420
But your wings were strong enough to endure any kind of wind.

145
00:14:34,420 --> 00:14:36,970
If I just let you be,

146
00:14:37,830 --> 00:14:42,770
you would have ridden the wind and flew up high into the sky.

147
00:14:43,830 --> 00:14:47,040
Since everything that happened wasn't your fault,

148
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:50,640
just leave it behind with me.

149
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:58,930
And from now on, let your wings carry you freely...

150
00:14:58,930 --> 00:15:01,290
wherever you want to go.

151
00:15:13,090 --> 00:15:15,720
She's currently at Sangmugwan with your son.

152
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:20,220
Don't send our own men. Use one of our spies in the militia to get rid of her.

153
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:23,910
Make it look like an internal conflict broke out and do it near the government building.

154
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:28,560
And make sure you kill her in front of my son.

155
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:30,850
I'll do that, Sir.

156
00:15:30,850 --> 00:15:36,330
Oh, she had a little kid with her. What shall I do about him?

157
00:15:36,330 --> 00:15:39,030
Get rid of him too if the timing is right—

158
00:15:40,670 --> 00:15:42,480
What's wrong?

159
00:15:46,130 --> 00:15:48,490
The housekeeper...

160
00:15:49,110 --> 00:15:53,760
asked if you're going to eat.

161
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:59,190
I'm working right now. Tell her I'll eat separately.

162
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:00,790
Okay.

163
00:16:12,670 --> 00:16:14,820
Eat lots.

164
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:16,970
Here.

165
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:20,360
Hurry and eat.

166
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:50,340
By any chance, are you Kim Myeong Hee?

167
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:52,000
Yes.

168
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:55,770
I have an urgent message for you.

169
00:16:58,290 --> 00:17:02,730
Hwang Hee Tae asked you to come quickly to this location.

170
00:17:03,390 --> 00:17:07,440
[Message from Hwang Hee Tae: Come to the service center now.]

171
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,110
Hee Tae did? For what reason?

172
00:17:11,110 --> 00:17:13,670
I got this as a message, so...

173
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:20,060
Since it's the service center, I guess it's about the funeral.

174
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:35,290
[Divorce Agreement]

175
00:17:35,290 --> 00:17:37,210
Divorce?

176
00:17:38,110 --> 00:17:42,130
- Are you crazy?
- I'm the most sane I've ever been.

177
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,280
I won't put up with this nonsense.

178
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:58,300
I'll mail you the papers again. If you want to talk to me, contact Attorney Choi from now on.

179
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:02,770
I'm going to take Jung Tae.

180
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:10,710
If you're going to leave, go by yourself. I have no intentions of giving you any child support.

181
00:18:10,710 --> 00:18:14,770
Then we'll have Jung Tae choose who he wants to live with.

182
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:20,490
What? Choose?

183
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,710
Jung Tae, come down!

184
00:18:24,430 --> 00:18:28,760
You better stop crossing the line.

185
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:31,820
Jung Tae! Hwang Jung Tae!

186
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:37,330
Ma'am, your son left urgently a while ago.

187
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:44,630
What's wrong?

188
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:05,350
Excuse me. Have you seen the girl that was over there?

189
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:12,490
Did you miss each other? She left as soon as she received the message.

190
00:19:12,490 --> 00:19:14,260
What message?

191
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:18,160
You sent her a message to come to the service center.

192
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:33,130
Kim Myeong Hee! You're here to see Hwang Hee Tae, right?

193
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:35,350
Yes. What's wrong?

194
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:40,210
The militia got the long-distance calls working again. Let me show you the way.

195
00:19:40,210 --> 00:19:44,200
Go straight and make a right.

196
00:20:04,430 --> 00:20:08,500
What is this bastard?! Let go!

197
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:10,790
- Jung Tae!
- Noona!

198
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:13,640
Noona, run!

199
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,950
I said, let go!

200
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:20,060
Jung Tae!

201
00:20:46,460 --> 00:20:50,960
- Jung Tae!
- Jung Tae! Jung Tae!

202
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:54,470
Which bastard is it? Who said to shoot my kid?

203
00:20:55,390 --> 00:20:58,650
- Who did this to my son?!
- It's you again?

204
00:20:58,650 --> 00:21:01,020
Is this what you did for your family?

205
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:04,170
What have you done now?

206
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:09,510
- Jung Tae!
- Don't come any closer!

207
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:11,770
Don't lay a finger on us.

208
00:21:16,450 --> 00:21:18,040
Hee Tae.

209
00:21:20,530 --> 00:21:22,340
You brought your car. Right, Mother?

210
00:21:22,340 --> 00:21:23,800
Let's get to the hospital first.

211
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:27,740
Jung Tae, can you hear me?

212
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,990
Jung Tae!

213
00:21:32,990 --> 00:21:35,890
Jung Tae... Jung Tae!

214
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:04,350
The orphan is not me but you.

215
00:22:04,350 --> 00:22:08,940
No one will choose you to be their family.

216
00:22:28,590 --> 00:22:31,430
Soo Ryun, bring that over there.

217
00:22:34,730 --> 00:22:36,670
Load it all up.

218
00:22:49,030 --> 00:22:51,730
I have another rat in my storeroom now.

219
00:22:51,730 --> 00:22:53,930
Father.

220
00:22:57,320 --> 00:23:02,210
Did you two decide to consider me a living corpse now?

221
00:23:02,210 --> 00:23:05,490
Father, it's not like that.

222
00:23:08,130 --> 00:23:10,310
I insisted we do it.

223
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:18,070
When I was little, you said this to me all the time.

224
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:20,730
"It's pointless to prosper alone."

225
00:23:20,730 --> 00:23:25,160
"We should grow together with the City of Gwangju."

226
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:30,950
I admired you for that and it really made me proud of our company, Changhwa Industrial.

227
00:23:33,970 --> 00:23:41,080
In my opinion, right now is the time.

228
00:23:52,820 --> 00:23:57,340
What can you possibly do with a cartful of supplies? Open all our storerooms.

229
00:23:57,350 --> 00:23:59,920
Take everything we have.

230
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:02,870
Father!

231
00:24:32,690 --> 00:24:34,980
Where did my sister go?

232
00:24:34,980 --> 00:24:39,200
Oh, are you awake? Your sister went to see Hee Tae real quick.

233
00:24:45,690 --> 00:24:50,450
My goodness! You still can't reach Mr. Park?

234
00:24:50,450 --> 00:24:54,970
The phone lines are cut off and the roads are blocked. There's no way we can reach someone outside the city.

235
00:24:54,970 --> 00:24:59,320
Then, will she be cremated right away? There won't even be a funeral?

236
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:01,310
What can we do?

237
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:07,130
Dead bodies are still pouring in. We can't keep her here much longer.

238
00:25:07,130 --> 00:25:12,890
Poor woman. She can't even see her family one last time.

239
00:25:12,890 --> 00:25:15,080
I feel so sorry for her.

240
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:19,640
Mother... Grandma...

241
00:25:28,820 --> 00:25:33,210
Do you have a map?

242
00:25:33,210 --> 00:25:35,770
The map you gave my father last time.

243
00:25:35,770 --> 00:25:37,860
Map? Why do you need a map all of a sudden?

244
00:25:37,860 --> 00:25:41,050
Excuse me. Can I report a missing person here?

245
00:25:41,050 --> 00:25:43,550
No, not here.

246
00:25:43,550 --> 00:25:48,420
Just a second. Why don't you try at the provincial government office?

247
00:25:48,420 --> 00:25:50,710
Thank you.

248
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:59,890
Shouldn't we be there until Jung Tae is out of his surgery?

249
00:25:59,890 --> 00:26:03,170
The doctor said he'll pull through. Once your father—

250
00:26:03,170 --> 00:26:07,720
Myeong Hee, Myeong Soo...

251
00:26:09,530 --> 00:26:12,190
Myeong Soo disappeared.

252
00:26:13,020 --> 00:26:14,610
What?

253
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:27,530
He probably went this way.

254
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:32,210
I'll look that way just in case.

255
00:26:34,450 --> 00:26:39,180
Try not to go this way since the army is standing post there.

256
00:26:51,380 --> 00:26:55,220
- Myeong Soo.
- Myeong Soo!

257
00:26:55,270 --> 00:27:00,070
- Kim Myeong Soo.
- Kim Myeong Soo!

258
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:02,060
Myeong Soo!

259
00:27:03,430 --> 00:27:06,110
- Myeong Soo!
- Kim Myeong Soo!

260
00:27:06,110 --> 00:27:08,050
Gosh, where did he go?

261
00:27:08,050 --> 00:27:10,100
Myeong Hee.

262
00:27:22,150 --> 00:27:24,510
The road splits.

263
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:31,260
I'll go this way. Myeong Hee, you look that way.

264
00:27:31,260 --> 00:27:35,270
Sun Min told us not to go that way.

265
00:27:35,270 --> 00:27:38,740
It's not marked on Myeong Soo's map, so there's no knowing which way he went.

266
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:43,320
Then, I'll go that way. Hee Tae, you go this way.

267
00:27:46,820 --> 00:27:49,470
Did you already forget my wedding prayer?

268
00:27:51,220 --> 00:27:55,360
I'm never going to do anything dangerous that will leave you behind.

269
00:27:56,770 --> 00:28:00,840
I'll go quickly just to check if Myeong Soo is there.

270
00:28:04,870 --> 00:28:10,510
Five minutes. Let's look separately for just five minutes and meet back here.

271
00:28:30,470 --> 00:28:32,510
Just five minutes.

272
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:38,770
We'll meet here in five minutes, okay?

273
00:28:47,490 --> 00:28:49,400
I'm sorry.

274
00:28:52,450 --> 00:28:54,560
It's our business.

275
00:29:05,100 --> 00:29:06,980
See you later.

276
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:12,480
Myeong Soo.

277
00:29:13,050 --> 00:29:14,740
Kim Myeong Soo!

278
00:30:13,290 --> 00:30:15,000
Put your hands up.

279
00:30:31,750 --> 00:30:34,130
Look thoroughly!

280
00:30:54,350 --> 00:30:57,630
Go to Naju first.

281
00:30:57,630 --> 00:31:00,050
I'll be right behind you.

282
00:31:00,050 --> 00:31:01,780
I don't want to.

283
00:31:03,010 --> 00:31:04,880
I'm not going to go alone.

284
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:05,980
Kim Myeong Soo.

285
00:31:05,980 --> 00:31:09,560
Father said he would be back too, but he didn't.

286
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:13,490
Let's go together, Sister!

287
00:31:15,330 --> 00:31:18,270
It's more dangerous to go with you.

288
00:31:18,270 --> 00:31:21,610
I'm a nurse, so no one will attack me.

289
00:31:21,610 --> 00:31:25,560
I'll explain it well to the army men and follow right behind you.

290
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:29,480
On the count of 3, you're going to run to Naju without looking back.

291
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:32,790
- Got it?
- I don't want to.

292
00:31:32,790 --> 00:31:34,650
I don't want to!

293
00:31:34,650 --> 00:31:36,840
Kim Mutt!

294
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:39,040
Listen to me carefully.

295
00:31:39,830 --> 00:31:42,050
I'll follow right behind you.

296
00:31:49,780 --> 00:31:51,510
Promise.

297
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:55,870
Promise?

298
00:31:55,870 --> 00:31:58,510
You promise you'll come right after me?

299
00:32:00,050 --> 00:32:04,770
Sister always keeps her promises.

300
00:32:04,770 --> 00:32:06,580
Don't you know?

301
00:32:38,700 --> 00:32:41,490
You're going to run on the count of 3.

302
00:32:42,610 --> 00:32:44,340
1,

303
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:47,450
2,

304
00:32:48,340 --> 00:32:50,000
3! Run!

305
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:09,970
What are you doing? Aren't you going to catch him?

306
00:33:09,970 --> 00:33:12,790
I'll go get him!

307
00:33:15,370 --> 00:33:18,050
That bastard, again.

308
00:33:41,570 --> 00:33:43,360
No!

309
00:33:57,730 --> 00:33:59,180
Go!

310
00:33:59,180 --> 00:34:01,030
Hurry and go!

311
00:34:03,850 --> 00:34:07,060
What are you doing? Go! Run!

312
00:34:47,320 --> 00:34:49,410
Who is this bastard?

313
00:34:49,410 --> 00:34:53,560
Seoul National University Medical School? What is an SNU med student doing here?

314
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:57,040
I'm from Gwangju.

315
00:34:57,040 --> 00:34:59,760
I was here because it's my hometown.

316
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:04,390
Hey, cut it out.

317
00:35:04,390 --> 00:35:07,790
You came here to lead a rebellion, didn't you?

318
00:35:07,790 --> 00:35:09,340
No.

319
00:35:09,340 --> 00:35:11,650
I'm really a Gwangju citizen.

320
00:35:11,650 --> 00:35:13,340
If you look at my identification card...

321
00:35:13,340 --> 00:35:14,830
Hey,

322
00:35:15,990 --> 00:35:18,070
just shoot.

323
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:51,770
Hwang Hee Tae?

324
00:36:00,440 --> 00:36:02,440
It is him.

325
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:05,390
The one who went to SNU with top marks. Hwang Hee Tae.

326
00:36:05,390 --> 00:36:08,920
- Is he someone you know?
- He's a big brother from my neighborhood.

327
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:11,190
I'm a Gwangju citizen.

328
00:36:13,390 --> 00:36:15,320
Get up.

329
00:36:21,190 --> 00:36:22,620
Where are you going?

330
00:36:22,620 --> 00:36:26,720
The order is to shoot any rebel to death immediately.

331
00:36:29,810 --> 00:36:34,130
Why don't we arrest him first to be sure?

332
00:36:34,130 --> 00:36:37,390
Let's take him and investigate him properly!

333
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:46,090
That way.

334
00:36:57,470 --> 00:37:00,060
If you want to live, just walk.

335
00:37:00,060 --> 00:37:02,080
Don't look back.

336
00:37:07,940 --> 00:37:11,300
Hey, did you empty out her pockets?

337
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:14,020
I'll go check.

338
00:37:14,020 --> 00:37:16,640
Take out anything that could be used for identification.

339
00:38:06,510 --> 00:38:10,690
Mister... Mister...

340
00:38:13,050 --> 00:38:15,130
My brother...

341
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:19,570
My brother Myeong Soo...

342
00:38:21,150 --> 00:38:23,510
is he alive?

343
00:38:38,010 --> 00:38:39,690
Yes.

344
00:38:42,040 --> 00:38:43,700
Yes.

345
00:39:46,150 --> 00:39:49,020
I can see the stars.

346
00:41:17,460 --> 00:41:21,350
[Chungmu, Kalguksu]

347
00:41:23,670 --> 00:41:26,630
Welcome! One person?

348
00:41:26,630 --> 00:41:28,530
[Missing Person]

349
00:41:28,530 --> 00:41:30,570
- They sang in perfect harmony.
- Yes. It must be the clear air.

350
00:41:30,570 --> 00:41:33,050
All right, you can leave them here.

