♫ and loneliness ♫

382
00:43:56,620 --> 00:44:02,570
[Missing person, Kim Myeong Hee, 26]

383
00:44:13,830 --> 00:44:19,130
[2021, Seoul]

384
00:44:19,130 --> 00:44:20,480
[Emergency Wing]

385
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:23,630
I was letting you off easy because you were a girl.

386
00:44:23,630 --> 00:44:25,780
Do you want to die?

387
00:44:25,780 --> 00:44:27,800
- Oh, no.
- What should we do?

388
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:31,490
I don't have to do something that is not part of a nurse's duties.

389
00:44:31,490 --> 00:44:35,130
You really need to stop talking back.

390
00:44:35,130 --> 00:44:37,140
Come on, now.

391
00:44:41,170 --> 00:44:42,140
Naughty hands.

392
00:44:42,140 --> 00:44:44,610
[Emergency Medicine]
[Hwang Hee Tae]

393
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:47,810
What is this?

394
00:44:47,810 --> 00:44:49,620
Move.

395
00:44:52,720 --> 00:44:54,960
Move.

396
00:44:54,960 --> 00:44:58,660
You're not going to move? This bastard wants to die.

397
00:45:03,460 --> 00:45:06,640
What got you so mad?

398
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:09,130
What are you—

399
00:45:09,130 --> 00:45:12,000
What are you doing? Call security.

400
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,830
Okay.

401
00:45:13,830 --> 00:45:16,820
Are you a patient or a guardian?

402
00:45:16,820 --> 00:45:19,190
Here, here... Calm down.

403
00:45:19,190 --> 00:45:25,330
[Emergency Medicine]
[Professor Hwang Hee Tae]

404
00:45:25,330 --> 00:45:27,330
Yes!

405
00:45:29,250 --> 00:45:32,260
Did I drop my phone earlier?

406
00:45:32,260 --> 00:45:35,650
It says the power's off.

407
00:45:35,650 --> 00:45:38,810
Why didn't Jung Tae call himself?

408
00:45:38,810 --> 00:45:41,780
Why is he making such a busy person call instead?

409
00:45:43,120 --> 00:45:45,400
Did he get on the plane?

410
00:45:47,380 --> 00:45:50,570
But it's nothing big, right?

411
00:45:50,570 --> 00:45:53,450
What is it that he wants to tell me in person?

412
00:45:53,450 --> 00:45:55,760
Hey!

413
00:45:55,760 --> 00:45:57,810
I found it.

414
00:45:57,810 --> 00:46:00,110
My head.

415
00:46:00,110 --> 00:46:04,560
I'll go right away. Send me the address.

416
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:06,830
See you later.

417
00:46:15,270 --> 00:46:17,550
I'm okay.

418
00:46:20,130 --> 00:46:21,980
Thank you.

419
00:46:28,250 --> 00:46:31,230
And... you are?

420
00:46:31,230 --> 00:46:35,060
You were looking for me?

421
00:46:35,060 --> 00:46:37,030
I was?

422
00:46:37,030 --> 00:46:39,120
I was?

423
00:46:39,960 --> 00:46:45,850
Oh, yes! You're that guy. The guy who administered CPR on a moving bus.

424
00:46:45,850 --> 00:46:48,060
So, how's the patient?

425
00:46:49,530 --> 00:46:51,750
Is he alive?

426
00:46:51,750 --> 00:46:56,270
No. He died last Saturday.

427
00:46:57,160 --> 00:47:00,990
[Emergency Medicine]
[Professor Hwang Hee Tae]

428
00:47:02,680 --> 00:47:06,870
Is that why you're quitting being an intern? Because your patient died?

429
00:47:06,870 --> 00:47:14,450
It's not just that. I don't think I'm qualified to be a doctor.

430
00:47:23,790 --> 00:47:25,810
I...

431
00:47:25,810 --> 00:47:30,520
I have somewhere to be, so I'll get straight to the point.

432
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:34,120
Your name is?

433
00:47:34,120 --> 00:47:35,390
It's Lee Seo On.

434
00:47:35,390 --> 00:47:38,840
Seo Woon. All right, Seo On.

435
00:47:45,400 --> 00:47:50,140
We're not people who decide between life and death.

436
00:47:50,140 --> 00:47:54,660
God makes the decisions.

437
00:47:54,660 --> 00:47:58,340
We're just doing our best in the time between.

438
00:47:58,340 --> 00:48:02,780
But you did your best in that time, not running away from it.

439
00:48:05,060 --> 00:48:07,600
I guarantee this,

440
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:13,320
but Seo On, you're going to be a great doctor.

441
00:48:15,190 --> 00:48:18,320
I need to be somewhere right now.

442
00:48:18,320 --> 00:48:21,650
If you're going to stay longer, turn the lights off on your way out.

443
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:43,610
[Punish the fake patriots!]
[The May 18 Gwangju uprising was the work of spies.]

444
00:48:47,340 --> 00:48:49,010
The light is green. You may cross now.

445
00:48:49,010 --> 00:48:52,170
Be careful crossing over.

446
00:49:01,960 --> 00:49:04,240
Seok Cheol!

447
00:49:06,320 --> 00:49:10,320
Sorry for asking you to come suddenly. I know you're busy.

448
00:49:10,320 --> 00:49:12,650
Not as busy as you are.

449
00:49:12,650 --> 00:49:15,310
Why have you lost so much weight? Take care of yourself.

450
00:49:15,310 --> 00:49:20,760
Come to the hospital for a check-up. Your employee discount expires this year.

451
00:49:21,460 --> 00:49:23,420
Let's go.

452
00:49:28,460 --> 00:49:30,830
But, Seok Cheol,

453
00:49:30,830 --> 00:49:35,850
how much is the fine if you tear down a banner these days?

454
00:49:35,850 --> 00:49:37,380
Not sure...

455
00:49:37,380 --> 00:49:41,050
Ask Soo Ryun for things regarding the law.

456
00:49:41,050 --> 00:49:43,170
Who? Lee Soo Ryun?

457
00:49:43,170 --> 00:49:45,910
She only knows about labor laws!

458
00:49:45,910 --> 00:49:49,650
All she did during law school was demonstrations.

459
00:49:49,650 --> 00:49:53,860
Earlier, I was shocked after I turned my cell phone on.

460
00:49:53,860 --> 00:49:56,590
I had so many missed calls from some old friends.

461
00:49:56,590 --> 00:50:01,030
And, strangely, they were all from Gwangju.

462
00:50:07,070 --> 00:50:11,460
Hey! Myeong Soo!

463
00:50:11,460 --> 00:50:14,840
Have you been well, Brother?

464
00:50:17,110 --> 00:50:20,910
Is today a special day? Are we holding a reunion?

465
00:50:39,970 --> 00:50:42,020
You found her?

466
00:50:43,620 --> 00:50:45,280
Yes.

467
00:51:12,210 --> 00:51:14,370
[Gwangju Jungbu Police Station]

468
00:51:14,370 --> 00:51:17,630
[Criminal Affairs Division]

469
00:51:17,630 --> 00:51:21,020
We found this note buried with the skeleton.

470
00:51:21,020 --> 00:51:25,700
According to the informant, this belonged to the deceased too.

471
00:51:25,700 --> 00:51:30,210
[Gwangju Metropolitan Police]

472
00:51:46,470 --> 00:51:48,700
Kyeong Soo.

473
00:53:50,070 --> 00:53:56,400
I, Kim Myeong Hee, refuse to be buried alive with Hwang Hee Tae.

474
00:54:07,560 --> 00:54:15,700
Lord, if something unexpected happens and we have to let go of each other's hands,

475
00:54:15,700 --> 00:54:21,650
please don't let the sorrow overwhelm the lives of those left behind.

476
00:54:22,830 --> 00:54:25,880
Even if the tears we shed alone

477
00:54:25,880 --> 00:54:32,710
fill up to our chins, please don't let us drown

478
00:54:32,710 --> 00:54:36,750
and give us the power and courage

479
00:54:36,750 --> 00:54:41,060
to swim safely throughout this life.

480
00:55:09,750 --> 00:55:13,290
As always, May has come.

481
00:55:13,290 --> 00:55:19,090
This year is the 41st May since I lost you, Myeong Hee.

482
00:55:27,030 --> 00:55:33,380
All this time, my life was like swimming during a rising tide.

483
00:55:34,540 --> 00:55:42,680
No matter how hard I tried, I couldn't move forward and I even tried to let myself drown.

484
00:55:56,080 --> 00:56:05,170
But when I woke up, that tide had pushed me back to that May inside my heart.

485
00:56:06,670 --> 00:56:10,290
It felt so cruel that I lived in resentment.

486
00:56:21,630 --> 00:56:28,670
For a very long time, I lived in regret and thought about what could've been.

487
00:56:28,670 --> 00:56:32,920
If I hadn't gone to Gwangju in May of that year,

488
00:56:32,920 --> 00:56:37,810
if I hadn't met you in Gwangju,

489
00:56:37,810 --> 00:56:42,230
if I hadn't let go of your hand in that split road,

490
00:56:42,230 --> 00:56:46,090
would you still be alive?

491
00:56:46,090 --> 00:56:52,560
But on this 41st May when you've finally returned,

492
00:56:52,560 --> 00:56:57,290
I now realize that I was the one who chose to do all of that.

493
00:56:58,390 --> 00:57:03,720
In May of that year, I chose to go to Gwangju

494
00:57:04,960 --> 00:57:09,870
and chose to love you with all my heart.

495
00:57:09,870 --> 00:57:15,140
I prayed every day that worse pains in life

496
00:57:15,140 --> 00:57:18,130
would come to me instead of you.

497
00:57:20,620 --> 00:57:26,720
If I had been the one to die in the crossroads of life and death and you had lived,

498
00:57:28,180 --> 00:57:33,270
you would've experienced the tides that I had experienced all this time.

499
00:57:34,550 --> 00:57:37,160
The life of the one who was left behind.

500
00:57:38,180 --> 00:57:41,720
Hence, I've finally realized...

501
00:57:41,720 --> 00:57:47,680
that what I experienced all this time was the Lord's way of answering my prayer.

502
00:57:47,680 --> 00:57:54,430
Those lonely and painful 41 years were merely...

503
00:57:54,430 --> 00:57:57,030
my love for you.

504
00:58:15,630 --> 00:58:19,820
[To Grandpa Myeong Hee]

505
00:58:20,710 --> 00:58:27,420
The remaining years of my life will be an answer to your prayer.

506
00:58:28,300 --> 00:58:34,290
No matter how many more times the rising tide pushes me back to that May,

507
00:58:34,290 --> 00:58:37,760
I have you here now.

508
00:58:37,760 --> 00:58:43,750
Until the day we meet again, I'll keep on swimming.

